output:
The issue is that `setFlippedX(true)` only flips the sprite's own texture — it does NOT flip child nodes. So the weapon will appear at `(+20, 0)` relative to the hero regardless of the flip, which looks wrong when the hero faces left.

If you want children to flip too, use negative scaleX instead:

Fixed code:
```typescript
const sprite = new cc.Sprite('res/hero.png');
sprite.setScaleX(-1);  // flips texture AND children
const child = new cc.Sprite('res/weapon.png');
child.setPosition(20, 0);
sprite.addChild(child);
```

Or keep `setFlippedX` but manually adjust child positions:
```typescript
const sprite = new cc.Sprite('res/hero.png');
sprite.setFlippedX(true);
const child = new cc.Sprite('res/weapon.png');
child.setPosition(-20, 0);  // negate x when flipped
sprite.addChild(child);
```

instruction:
Fix the bug in this code that adds sprites to a batch node:

```typescript
const batch = new cc.SpriteBatchNode('res/atlas_a.png', 100);
this.addChild(batch);

const s1 = new cc.Sprite('res/hero.png'); // from atlas_a
const s2 = new cc.Sprite('res/enemy.png'); // from a DIFFERENT texture!
batch.addChild(s1);
batch.addChild(s2);
```

output:
The bug is that `s2` uses a different texture (`res/enemy.png`) than the batch node (`res/atlas_a.png`). All sprites in a `cc.SpriteBatchNode` must share the same texture. Adding a sprite with a different texture will cause rendering errors or crashes.

Fixed code:
```typescript
const batch = new cc.SpriteBatchNode('res/atlas_a.png', 100);
this.addChild(batch);

// Both sprites must use frames from the same atlas texture
cc.spriteFrameCache.addSpriteFrames('res/atlas_a.plist', 'res/atlas_a.png');

const s1 = new cc.Sprite(cc.spriteFrameCache.getSpriteFrame('hero.png'));
const s2 = new cc.Sprite(cc.spriteFrameCache.getSpriteFrame('enemy.png'));
batch.addChild(s1);
batch.addChild(s2);
```

Both `hero.png` and `enemy.png` must be frames within the `atlas_a` spritesheet. If they're from different textures, use separate batch nodes or add them directly to the layer.

instruction:
Find and fix the bug in this sprite frame swap:

```typescript
